URGENT HELP! - can't disable alarm

Hope someone can help, or have an idea!

i've got a 1997 146 1.6TS , alfa factory alarm
1 x red key with remote
1 x brown master key - no remote

Problem is when i press the button on the remote key, the little red
light on the key blinks, but doesn't disable the alarm!

I had this problem 2 weeks ago and changed the batteries in the remote
key, this worked ok so i thought nothing more of it, but it's done it
again today, so i can't get into the car without setting off the alarm!

i know i can get into the car ok with the physical key and should be
able to start it as well, but obviously the alarm will sound! and
probably not stop either!

any ideas on a way around this? , i've spoken to a dealer who suggested
waiting until the car cools down a little, or trying to shade the
windscreen area and try it again as the sunlight might be affecting it
in some way, i'll try that later on.

other than that, is there another way of disableing the alarm system or
just the sounder? , i know the alarm is located in the rear wing, can
you get to the box at all under the car? , or can you pull a fuse on
the sounder unit?

any help very much appreciated! , as i'm a little stuck at work at the
moment!

thanks

