<POST>
<POSTER> Steve Golab </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2005-09-05T18:28:00 </POSTDATE>
In the boot, offside, there should be a lift up flap on trim, revealing
the alarm box. You should have a small 'round' key which fits the socket
under the flap. This will disable the alarm.
Had a problem with my 146; 10 mins after parking, alarm goes off. Turns
out to be bonnet pin switch - when hot, expands enough make contact, but
as it cooled and contracted, no longer made contact and alarm goes off!
HTH
